@bffUrl = http://localhost:8080
@channel = general
@username = flowtester
@password = password123

### Register user through BFF
POST {{bffUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "displayName": "Flow Tester",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Login through BFF
# Copy the token from the response into the token variable below.
POST {{bffUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Set token manually after login
@token = paste-token-here

### Check current user from JWT claims
GET {{bffUrl}}/api/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Trigger full BFF -> message-service -> RabbitMQ -> bot-service -> message-service flow
POST {{bffUrl}}/api/messages
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "channel": "{{channel}}",
  "content": "hej bot"
}

### Wait about one second, then verify original message and PulseBot response
GET {{bffUrl}}/api/messages?channel={{channel}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
